    {
      "title": "The Two Emphasis Nuns",
      "titleArabic": "نونا التوكيد",
      "content": [
        "Arabic has two emphasis nuns: the heavy nun (نون التوكيد الثقيلة - نَّ) and the light nun (نون التوكيد الخفيفة - نْ).",
        "They attach to present tense verbs to emphasize the action, common after oaths and with لَام التوكيد."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Heavy nun (الثقيلة): لَيَفْعَلَنَّ (he will surely do)",
        "Light nun (الخفيفة): لَيَفْعَلَنْ (he will surely do)",
        "Heavy is more emphatic than light",
        "Both cause the verb to be مبني (invariable)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "وَاللهِ لَأَذْهَبَنَّ", "english": "By Allah, I will surely go" },
        { "arabic": "لَيَفْعَلَنَّ الْخَيْرَ", "english": "He will surely do good" },
        { "arabic": "لَتُسْأَلُنَّ عَنْ أَعْمَالِكُمْ", "english": "You will surely be asked about your deeds" },
        { "arabic": "لَيُنْصَرَنْ الْمَظْلُومُ", "english": "The oppressed will surely be helped" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Conditions and Usage",
      "titleArabic": "شروط استعمال نون التوكيد",
      "content": [
        "The emphasis nuns attach to present tense verbs (المضارع) in specific contexts: after oaths with لَام, with conditional لَا, or expressing strong determination.",
        "The verb ending changes when the nun is attached: يَفْعَلُ → يَفْعَلَنَّ."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "After oath + لام: وَاللهِ لَأَفْعَلَنَّ",
        "With لَا in negative commands: لَا تَفْعَلَنَّ",
        "Verb becomes مبني على الفتح before نّ",
        "Common in Quran: لَنَسْفَعًا (We will surely drag)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "لَا تَحْسَبَنَّ اللهَ غَافِلًا", "english": "Do not think Allah is unaware" },
        { "arabic": "لَيَسْجُنُنَّهُ", "english": "They will surely imprison him" },
        { "arabic": "لَنَسْفَعًا بِالنَّاصِيَةِ", "english": "We will surely drag by the forelock" },
